#. <section class="sutta" id="sn36.8"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn36.8:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 36"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 36"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn36.8:0.2"
msgid "1. Sagāthāvagga"
msgstr "1. With Verses"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn36.8:0.3"
msgid "8. Dutiyagelaññasutta"
msgstr "8. The Infirmary (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Vesālī, at the Great Wood, in the "
"hall with the peaked roof."

msgctxt "sn36.8:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho bhagavā sāyanhasamayaṃ paṭisallānā vuṭṭhito yena gilānasālā "
"tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi."
msgstr ""
"Then in the late afternoon, the Buddha came out of retreat and went to the "
"infirmary, where he sat down on the seat spread out,"

msgctxt "sn36.8:1.3"
msgid "Nisajja kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "and addressed the mendicants:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:2.1"
msgid "“Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno kālaṃ āgameyya."
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant should await their time mindful and aware."

msgctxt "sn36.8:2.2"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī."
msgstr "This is my instruction to you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:3.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant mindful?"

msgctxt "sn36.8:3.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāye kāyānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, "
"vineyya loke abhijjhādomanassaṃ;"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant meditates by observing an aspect of the body—keen, "
"aware, and mindful, rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn36.8:3.3"
msgid "vedanāsu vedanānupassī viharati …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of feelings …"

msgctxt "sn36.8:3.4"
msgid "citte cittānupassī viharati …"
msgstr "They meditate observing an aspect of the mind …"

msgctxt "sn36.8:3.5"
msgid ""
"dhammesu dhammānupassī viharati ātāpī sampajāno satimā, vineyya loke "
"abhijjhādomanassaṃ."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing an aspect of principles—keen, aware, and mindful, "
"rid of desire and aversion for the world."

msgctxt "sn36.8:3.6"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sato hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is mindful."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.214"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:4.1"
msgid "Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti?"
msgstr "And how is a mendicant aware?"

msgctxt "sn36.8:4.2"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu abhikkante paṭikkante sampajānakārī hoti … pe … "
"bhāsite tuṇhībhāve sampajānakārī hoti."
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant acts with situational awareness when going out and "
"coming back; when looking ahead and aside; when bending and extending the "
"limbs; when bearing the outer robe, bowl and robes; when eating, drinking, "
"chewing, and tasting; when urinating and defecating; when walking, standing, "
"sitting, sleeping, waking, speaking, and keeping silent."

msgctxt "sn36.8:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno hoti."
msgstr "That’s how a mendicant is aware."

msgctxt "sn36.8:4.4"
msgid "Sato, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sampajāno kālaṃ āgameyya."
msgstr "A mendicant should await their time mindful and aware."

msgctxt "sn36.8:4.5"
msgid "Ayaṃ vo amhākaṃ anusāsanī."
msgstr "This is my instruction to you."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃ satassa sampajānassa appamattassa "
"ātāpino pahitattassa viharato uppajjati sukhā vedanā."
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is meditating like this—mindful, aware, diligent, keen, "
"and resolute—if pleasant feelings arise, they understand:"

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.3"
msgid "‘uppannā kho myāyaṃ sukhā vedanā;"
msgstr "‘A pleasant feeling has arisen in me."

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.4"
msgid "sā ca kho paṭicca, no appaṭicca."
msgstr "That’s dependent, not independent."

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.5"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.6"
msgid "Imameva phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on this very contact."

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho pana phasso anicco saṅkhato paṭiccasamuppanno."
msgstr "But this contact is impermanent, conditioned, dependently originated."

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.8"
msgid ""
"Aniccaṃ kho pana saṅkhataṃ paṭiccasamuppannaṃ phassaṃ paṭicca uppannā sukhā "
"vedanā kuto niccā bhavissatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"So how could a pleasant feeling be permanent, since it has arisen dependent "
"on contact that is impermanent, conditioned, and dependently originated?’"

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.9"
msgid ""
"So phasse ca sukhāya ca vedanāya aniccānupassī viharati, vayānupassī "
"viharati, virāgānupassī viharati, nirodhānupassī viharati, "
"paṭinissaggānupassī viharati."
msgstr ""
"They meditate observing impermanence, vanishing, dispassion, cessation, and "
"letting go in contact and pleasant feeling."

msgctxt "sn36.8:5.10"
msgid ""
"Tassa phasse ca sukhāya ca vedanāya aniccānupassino viharato, vayānupassino "
"viharato, virāgānupassino viharato, nirodhānupassino viharato, "
"paṭinissaggānupassino viharato yo phasse ca sukhāya ca vedanāya rāgānusayo, "
"so pahīyati."
msgstr ""
"As they do so, they give up the underlying tendency for greed for contact "
"and pleasant feeling."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:6.1"
msgid "Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno evaṃ satassa … pe …"
msgstr ""
"While a mendicant is meditating like this—mindful, aware, diligent, keen, "
"and resolute—if painful feelings arise …"

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.2"
msgid "viharato uppajjati dukkhā vedanā … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.3"
msgid "uppajjati adukkhamasukhā vedanā."
msgstr "if neutral feelings arise, they understand:"

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.4"
msgid "So evaṃ pajānāti:"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.5"
msgid "‘uppannā kho myāyaṃ adukkhamasukhā vedanā;"
msgstr "‘A neutral feeling has arisen in me."

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.6"
msgid "sā ca kho paṭicca, no appaṭicca."
msgstr "That’s dependent, not independent."

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.7"
msgid "Kiṃ paṭicca?"
msgstr "Dependent on what?"

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.8"
msgid "Imameva phassaṃ paṭicca."
msgstr "Dependent on this very contact."

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.9"
msgid "(Yathā purimasutte, tathā vitthāretabbo.)"
msgstr "(Expand in detail as in the previous discourse.)"

msgctxt "sn36.8:6.10"
msgid ""
"Kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni anabhinanditāni "
"sītībhavissantī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life is over, everything "
"that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become cool right "
"here.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn36.8:7.1"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, telañca paṭicca vaṭṭiñca paṭicca telappadīpo "
"jhāyeyya, "
msgstr "Suppose an oil lamp depended on oil and a wick to burn. "

msgctxt "sn36.8:7.2"
msgid "tasseva telassa ca vaṭṭiyā ca pariyādānā anāhāro nibbāyeyya;"
msgstr ""
"As the oil and the wick are used up, it would be extinguished due to lack of "
"fuel."

msgctxt "sn36.8:7.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayamāno ‘"
"kāyapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti. Jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ "
"vedayamāno ‘jīvitapariyantikaṃ vedanaṃ vedayāmī’ti pajānāti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, feeling the end of the body approaching, a mendicant "
"understands: ‘I feel the end of the body approaching.’ Feeling the end of "
"life approaching, they understand: ‘I feel the end of life approaching.’"

msgctxt "sn36.8:7.4"
msgid ""
"‘Kāyassa bhedā uddhaṃ jīvitapariyādānā idheva sabbavedayitāni "
"anabhinanditāni sītībhavissantī’ti pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘When my body breaks up and my life is over, everything "
"that’s felt, since I no longer take pleasure in it, will become cool right "
"here.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn36.8:7.5"
msgid "Aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
